    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - INSTALLING REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INSTALLING REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Install rear oil seal carrier as follows:</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new gasket into rear oil seal carrier.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach guide to crankshaft flange and tighten bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rear oil seal carrier and secure to crankcase by finger-tightening the mounting
                bolts (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050710">7.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050709" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2371" filename="../figeg2/EG2371.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.9.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Rear Oil Seal Carrier Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Rear Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050710" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3071" filename="../figeg3/EG3071.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.10.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Rear Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Rear Oil Seal Carrier Mounting Bolts (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Guide</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install driver and tighten driver nut to center carrier (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050711">7.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate/twist carrier to even carrier with cylinder block oil pan rail. Use straight edge to
                verify.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When the rear oil seal carrier is level, tighten the mounting bolts to special torque value
                (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050712">7.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear oil seal installation tool.</para>
            <figure id="ef1050711" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3063" filename="../figeg3/EG3063.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.11.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Rear Oil Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Driver</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Crankcase</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050712" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3070" filename="../figeg3/EG3070.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.12.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Straightedge</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Driver</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut any access O-Ring material off from rear oil seal carrier (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e105_136.xml" xrefid="ef1050713">7.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
